-- Murphy Oil to Shut and Evacuate ThunderHawk, Medusa, FrontRunner
-- B y   A s j y l y n   L o d e r
-- 2012-08-26T16:36:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-08-26/murphy-oil-to-shut-and-evacuate-thunderhawk-medusa-frontrunner.html
Murphy Oil Co. (MUR)  said today that it
has shut in and is evacuating its ThunderHawk facility in the
Gulf of Mexico due to the approach of Tropical Storm Isaac, and
will evacuate additional facilities tomorrow.  “ThunderHawk is now shut in with all crews being evacuated
today,” said Barry Jeffery, a spokesman for the company, in an
e-mail today. “Medusa and FrontRunner will be shut down and
evacuated on Monday.”  To contact the reporter on this story:
Asjylyn Loder in New York at 
 aloder@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Sylvia Wier at   swier@bloomberg.net  